The paper discusses deep learning algorithms for segmentation and reconstruction of neural circuits from electron microscopy images. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel convolutional recurrent neural network module, which is a combination of convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and recurrent neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for connectomics analysis, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for connectomics analysis, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
